Interface Movable

All Superinterfaces:
GameObject, java.io.Serializable
All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractMovable, Player
public interface Movable
extends GameObject

The Movable interface is implemented by GameObjects to give them functionality and capabilities required for the Objects to move, and signify to the Engine that this Object can move. Classes should extends AbstractGameObject rather than implementing this interface.

Since:
April 9, 2011
Version:
1.0.0.1 : April 10, 2011
Author:
Mihail Kurbako, Dan Zapornikov
See Also:
GameObject, AbstractMovable

moveTo

void moveTo(double x,
            double y)
Sets this GameObjects x and y coordinate value to the given values. The Object will be moved next time the Engine processes the GameObject.

Parameters:
x - The new value for this GameObject's X coordinate.
y - The new value for this GameObject's Y coordinate.

canMoveTo

boolean canMoveTo(double x,
                  double y)
Checks whether this GameObject can move to the specified coordinates. This will always return false if the given coordinates are beyond the edge of the GameObject's enclosing World.

Parameters:
x - The potential value for the GameObject's X coordinate.
y - The potential value for the GameObject's Y coordinate.
Returns:
true if it is able, false otherwise.
